########################################################################################################################
# Help for debug mode
########################################################################################################################
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[CTRL+X+Z]  nixlper_debug_toggle : toggle nixlper debug mode on/off
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
When enabled, debug mode prints a summary of all resolved NIXLPER_* variables.
The NIXLPER_DEBUG variable persists for the current shell session.
To enable permanently, set NIXLPER_DEBUG=true via nconf.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ndebug <function> [args...]  : trace a single nixlper function call with set -x
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Wraps the named function in set -x / set +x so only that function's execution is
traced — avoids the noise of global set -x in an interactive shell.

  Examples:
    ndebug navigate
    ndebug _check_update
    ndebug _display_existing_bookmarks

Output format:
  [NIXLPER DEBUG] Tracing: <function> <args>
  ──────────────────────────────────────────
  + <traced lines>
  ──────────────────────────────────────────
  [NIXLPER DEBUG] Exit code: <N>

If the function is not found, ndebug prints an error and suggests using
  declare -F | grep nixlper
to list all loaded nixlper functions.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ndbconf  : show resolved values of all NIXLPER_* variables (without toggling debug mode)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Configuration:
  NIXLPER_DEBUG   bool   false   Enable debug mode (config summary at login, ndebug tracing)
                                 Set via: nconf  or  export NIXLPER_DEBUG=true
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
